OL,3,CAsylum system delays and backlogs have
OL,4,Cwasted taxpayers' money, watchdog finds
OL,6,FMeanwhile, the NAO found 41% of the
OL,7,F5,000 were of those who had their
OL,8,Fclaims refused but had not been
OL,9,Fremoved from the country, leading to
OL,10,F"significant costs" for accommodation
OL,11,Fand support.
OL,13,FReasons why asylum seekers with
OL,14,Frefused claims cannot be removed
OL,15,Finclude missing identity documents and
OL,16,Fcompliance of foreign governments,
OL,17,Feven if agreements are in place.
