OL,3,CAsylum system delays and backlogs have
OL,4,Cwasted taxpayers' money, watchdog finds
OL,6,F"Increases in speed of processing have
OL,7,Fsometimes come at the expense of the
OL,8,Fquality of decisions and improvements
OL,9,Fin one area have shunted problems
OL,10,Felsewhere.
OL,12,F"There has also been no realistic
OL,13,Fapproach to the fact that, in a
OL,14,Fsignificant number of cases it is not
OL,15,Fpossible to return people whose claims
OL,16,Fhave been refused. As a result, the
OL,17,Fsystem has incurred significant costs
OL,18,F` primarily on accommodation and
OL,19,Fsupport ` that might have been
OL,20,Favoided."
